revision.text:
The 33rd [[Cuban National Series]] saw further dominance from the previous year's group winners: [[Pinar del Río (baseball team)|Pinar del Río]], [[Industriales]], [[Villa Clara (baseball team)|Villa Clara]] and [[Santiago de Cuba (baseball team)|Santiago de Cuba]]. Among them, only Pinar del Río won its group by fewer than seven games, in a 65-game season.
After winning their semifinal series, Villa Clara and Industriales fought to a seventh and deciding game. Villa Clara ultimately won, after Jorge Fumero knocked in [[Ariel Pestano]] for the game's winning run.
