{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}} {{Infobox football league season |competition=[[A-Division (Bhutan)]] |season=2008 |winners=[[Transport United]] |relegated= |continentalcup1=[[2009 AFC President's Cup|AFC President's Cup]] |continentalcup1 qualifiers=[[Transport United]] |continentalcup2= |continentalcup2 qualifiers= |league topscorer= |biggest home win= |biggest away win= |highest scoring= |matches=56 |total goals= |longest wins= |title= |longest unbeaten=[[Yeedzin F.C.|Yeedzin]] (14 matches) |longest losses= |prevseason=[[2007 A-Division|2007]] |nextseason=[[2009 A-Division|2009]] }}
The 2008 season of the [[A-Division (Bhutan)|Bhutanese A-Division]] was the fourteenth recorded season of top-flight football in [[Bhutan]]. The league was won by [[Yeedzin FC]], their first ever title, and the first time a team other than [[Transport United]] had won the league in five years.<ref name="RSSSFChamp">{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesb/bhutanchamp.html |title=Bhutan - List of Champions |last=Schöggl |first=Hans |last2=Abbink |first2=Dinant |date=28 May 2014 |website=www.rsssf.com |publisher=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]] |accessdate=27 June 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140717020149/http://rsssf.com/tablesb/bhutanchamp.html |archivedate=17 July 2014 |df= }}</ref> Yeedzin qualified as Bhutan's representative in the [[2009 AFC President's Cup]].<ref name="AFC">{{cite web|url=http://www.the-afc.com/en/afc-presidents-cup-2009-previous-competitions/afc-presidents-cup-2009/afc-presidents-cup-2009-schedule-results?id=61&type=Stage|title=2009 AFC President's Cup Schedule and Results|website=the-afc.com|publisher=[[Asian Football Confederation]]|accessdate=16 July 2014}}</ref>
