'''Avándaro Golf Club''' ({{lang-es|Club de Golf Avandaro}}) is a [[golf course]] located in the [[Valle de Bravo, Mexico State|Valle de Bravo]] state of [[Mexico]]. Located {{convert|110|mi|km|abbr=on}} west of [[Mexico City]], it hosted the [[eventing]] portion of the [[Equestrian at the 1968 Summer Olympics|equestrian]] competition for the [[1968 Summer Olympics]].

During the 1968 Games, the club had stables for 120 horses to have the event on the course and the neighboring countryside.

