{{Infobox venue | stadium_name = Bear Down Gym | nickname = Bear Down Gym | image = [[File:Bear Down Gym.jpg|200px]] | caption = Bear Down Gymnasium | fullname = Bear Down Gymnasium | location = [[Tucson, Arizona]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = 1925 | built = | opened = 1926 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[University of Arizona]] | operator = University of Arizona | surface = | construction_cost = US$130,000 | architect = [[Lyman & Place]]/[[Roy Place]]<ref name=appendixA/> | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = [[Clinton Campbell]]<ref name=appendixA/> | project_manager = | main_contractors = | former_names = | tenants = [[Arizona Wildcats men's basketball]] (1926–1973) | seating_capacity = 6,000 (peak) {{Citation needed|date=February 2011}} | embedded = {{Infobox NRHP | embed = yes | name = Men's Gymnasium, University of Arizona | nrhp_type = | location = [[University of Arizona]] campus [[Tucson, Arizona]] | coordinates = {{coord|32|13|52|N|110|57|0|W|region:US_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = Arizona | built = 1926 | architect = | architecture = | added = October 4, 1990 | area = {{convert|0.3|acre|sigfig=1}} | governing_body = Local | refnum = 90001526<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|2009a}}</ref> }} }}
'''Bear Down Gym''', originally known as '''Men's Gymnasium''', is a 300-seat multi-purpose arena in [[Tucson, Arizona]]. It opened in 1926. It was home to the [[University of Arizona]] Wildcats basketball team. It was replaced when the [[McKale Center]] opened in 1973. It is listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]].
Bear Down Gym is also famous for its inclusion in the 1984 blockbuster film [[Revenge of the Nerds]]. It was the gymnasium of the fictional "Adams College" and also temporary home to the Nerds after they were kicked out of their original Freshmen home ([[Cochise Hall]]).
It was designed by [[Lyman & Place]]/[[Roy Place]], architect, and was built by [[Clinton Campbell]].<ref name=appendixA>{{cite web|url=http://www.cdarc.org/pdf/scvnha/appendix_A.pdf |title=Appendix A: Descriptions of Important Historic Sites}}, part of {{cite web|url=http://www.cdarc.org/pdf/scvnha/cover.pdf |title=Feasibility Study for the Santa Cruz Valley National Heritage Area |publisher=Center for Desert Archaeology |editor=Jonathan Mabry |date=April 2005}}</ref>
It was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] as '''Men's Gymnasium, University of Arizona''' in 1990.<ref name=nris/>
The building has been renovated and updated to accommodate the growing needs of University of Arizona students, including housing resources for students such as the Think Tank, where students are tutored.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.wildcat.arizona.edu/article/2015/07/places-to-know-campus|title=Places to know on campus|last=McGlothlin|first=David|date=2015-07-15|work=The Daily Wildcat|access-date=2017-10-02|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=}}</ref> Plans are in the works to add a three-story building over the spot currently holding an old swimming pool.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.wildcat.arizona.edu/article/2017/04/bear-down-gym-gears-up-for-major-improvements|title=Bear Down Gym gears up for major improvements|last=Heffernan|first=Marissa|date=2017-04-23|work=Daily Wildcat|access-date=2017-10-02|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=}}</ref>
