{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2017}} {{Use Indian English|date=July 2017}} {{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Duleep Cricket School | nickname = Duleep Ground | country = India | image = | location = [[Porbandar]], [[Saurashtra (region)|Saurashtra]] | establishment = 1947 | seating_capacity = n/a | end1 = | end2 = n/a | club1 = [[Saurashtra cricket team]] | year1 = 1968-1986 | date = 27 August, | year = 2015 | source = http://www.espncricinfo.com/india/content/ground/58389.html Cricinfo }}
'''Duleep Cricket School''' is a cricket ground in [[Porbandar]], [[Saurashtra (region)|Saurashtra]]. The ground is also home ground of [[Saurashtra cricket team]]. The ground hosted a six cricket matches from 1968 to 1986 before falling of the record. The ground is named after great Indian cricketer and [[Prince of Nawanagar]] Kumar Shri [[Duleepsinhji]].
In 2011, [[Jay Mehta]], the co-owner of [[Kolkata Knight Riders]], along with the Porbandar District Cricket Association decided to develop the Duleep Cricket School and to regain the domestic status. The proposal includes built outfield, dressing rooms, water-logging problems as well as pavilion and indoor cricket facilities.<ref>[http://deshgujarat.com/2011/04/11/mehta-sports-to-develop-porbandar-cricket-ground-for-7-10-crore/ Jay Mehta a KKR co-owner to develop Porbandar ground]</ref><ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/rajkot/KKR-co-owner-to-develop-Porbandar-ground-for-7-cr/articleshow/7936221.cms KKR co-owner to develop Porbandar ground for 7 cr]</ref><ref>[http://www.internationalsportsturf.com/uploads/docs/ISTeC_Newsletter.pdf Duleep Cricket Ground]</ref>
