{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Estadio Max Augustín | nickname = | image = Estadio Max Augustín.jpg | image_size = 280px | fullname = Estadio Regional Max Augustín | location = [[Iquitos]], [[Peru]] | built =1942 | opened =1942 | renovated =2005 | expanded =2005 | owner =Regional government | operator =Instituto Peruano del Deporte | surface = Artificial turf | construction_cost =[[nuevo sol|S/.]]18,000,000 | tenants =[[Colegio Nacional Iquitos]] | seating_capacity =24,576<ref name="Caps"/> | dimensions =105 x 68 m }}
The '''Estadio Max Augustín''' is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Iquitos]], [[Peru]]. It is the home ground of the [[football (soccer)]] team [[Colegio Nacional Iquitos]] and several other [[Copa Perú]] teams from Iquitos and the surrounding region. The stadium holds 24,576 people.<ref name="Caps">{{cite web|url=http://www.fussballtempel.net/conmebol/PER.html |title=Peru |work=fussballtempel.net |accessdate=2008-01-16}}</ref> It was built in 1942 and renovated in 2005. The stadium has artificial turf, an artificial running track, and was a venue in the [[2005 FIFA U-17 World Championship]]
