'''Jennifer Chieng''' (born April 29, 1986) is a [[boxing|boxer]] from the [[Federated States of Micronesia]]. She competed at the [[2016 Summer Olympics]] in the [[Boxing at the 2016 Summer Olympics – Women's lightweight|women's lightweight]] event, in which she was eliminated in the round of 16 by [[Mikaela Mayer]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Jennifer Chieng |url=https://www.rio2016.com/en/athlete/jennifer-chieng |website=Rio 2016 |accessdate=August 21, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160821233938/https://www.rio2016.com/en/athlete/jennifer-chieng |archivedate=August 21, 2016 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Women's Light (57-60kg) - Standings |url=https://www.rio2016.com/en/boxing-standings-bx-womens-light-57-60kg |website=Rio 2016 |accessdate=August 21, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160821234027/https://www.rio2016.com/en/boxing-standings-bx-womens-light-57-60kg |archivedate=August 21, 2016 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> She was the flag bearer for her country at the [[2016 Summer Olympics Parade of Nations|Parade of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Rio 2016 Opening Ceremony - Flag Bearers|url=https://stillmed.olympic.org/media/Document%20Library/OlympicOrg/News/2016/08/2016-08-05-Rio-2016-Opening-Ceremony-Flag-Bearers.pdf#_ga=1.141545717.655653539.1470508014|publisher=International Olympic Committee|accessdate=August 21, 2016}}</ref>

