{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Meadow Road | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Beeston, Nottinghamshire]] | establishment = 1867 <small>(first recorded match)</small> | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1870 | club1 = [[Gentlemen of the North]] | date = 31 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/312.html Ground profile }}
'''Meadow Road''' was a [[cricket]] ground in [[Beeston, Nottinghamshire]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1867, when the Gentlemen of Nottinghamshire played the Gentlemen of Lincolnshire.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/312_misc.html Other matches played on Meadow Road]</ref> In 1870, the ground hosted its only [[first-class cricket|first-class]] match when the [[Gentlemen of the North]] played the [[Gentlemen of the South]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/312_f.html First-Class matches played on Meadow Road]</ref> The last recorded match on the ground came in 1961 when Nottinghamshire Juniors played Derbyshire Juniors.
The ground is today covered by a [[technology park]].
