{{Infobox handball club | clubname = RK Bjelovar | image = | fullname = Rukometni klub Bjelovar | short name = | founded = 1955 | ground = Školsko-sportska dvorana Bjelovar | capacity = 1,500 | chairman = Željko Maletić | manager = Željko Vidaković | league = [[Croatian Premier Handball League|Dukat Premijer Liga]] | season = | position = | website = | colour1 = | colour2 = | pattern_la1 = _bluelower | pattern_b1 = _whiteshoulders | pattern_ra1 = _bluelower | pattern_sh1 = | leftarm1 = ffffff | body1 = 0000ff | rightarm1 = ffffff | shorts1 = ffffff | pattern_la2 = _blueshoulders | pattern_b2 = _blueshoulders | pattern_ra2 = _blueshoulders | pattern_sh2 = | leftarm2 = ffffff | body2 = ffffff | rightarm2 = ffffff | shorts2 = ffffff }}
'''RK Bjelovar''' (Rukometni Klub Bjelovar) is a [[team handball]] club from [[Bjelovar]], [[Croatia]] formed in 1955. The club currently competes in the [[Croatian Second League of Handball]] (North) and the [[Croatian Handball Cup]].
During [[Communist Yugoslavia]], the club was known as '''Partizan''', named after the [[Second World War]]'s [[Yugoslav Partisans]]. After Croatian independence in 1991, the current name was adopted. Despite being the most successful club in Yugoslavia, it has had little success since the 1980 season and has been thoroughly eclipsed by [[RK Zagreb]] in modern Croatian handball. {{location map | Croatia | caption = Location of Bjelovar in Croatia | lat = 45.91 | long = 16.84 }}
